content.detailedDescription: I was taking my trash to the road. i observe a lot and see many strange things. being tonight is the time i really noticed something that made the hair on the back of my neck stand up. i love the darkness and watching the stars and i don't take nature for granted. i was on the front of my yard and i looked to the east of my home above near the big dipper but still a good distant away a triangle shape. the lights were bright and was pulsing like a heart does in our bodies. all the while i noticed a small white orb looking object went straight to the main object catching my eyes. the top light was red and the outlines could faintly be seen in green. when i looked further south i noticed seven more the same. they're all aligned side by side. come on satellites never do that! i am extremely paying attention to the night sky and this is the first time i had my breath taken away. they all pulsates. i walked to my back yard getting a better glimpse. they had good gaps but we're still distance apart perfectly in between and forming and o in the night sky. i held my breath because for some reason a deep feeling inside kept telling me to look closely tonight in the stars and i did. while i stood there in my backyard with chills, along the tree lines i saw residue of what looks like vapor smoke but no flames. i seen the triangular shape falling fast in a straight line for the ground. i thought hell i'm just seeing stuff! i didn't hear a crash or a boom. the night was silent around me and i was in disbelief. the object was so fast but seemed so slow at the same time and the lights were exactly the same as the ones right now in the sky as i write this. i seen many sightings but this sighting it's disturbing me... i never lost sight of the objects they're still hanging out.... takes more than a naked eye just to see.
content.summary: Aligned in they sky

content.summary: It looked like a wide penny and it was blue with sparks

content.detailedDescription: I was watching nasa's solar observation satellite through its lens from my computer, when i viewed a large object circling around the sun. originally i thought it was an earth based satellite, due to its shape, so i ignored it. upon further observations' however, i realized that this object was far larger than a satellite. the angle distance and speed gained my attention as well. it curved around the sun near the top, circling around the backside, followed by a massive solar eruption, where this object would have been. after making its way from the back of the sun towards the direction of earth, a second massive eruption took place directly behind it. i was able to get a closer look when it swung around. it was spherical in shape with a large wing like structure, and pulsated all across the surface in even increments. the first nasa monitor from the satellite showed a standard lens view, i would imagine. i took a few video clips' of this monitor, which gave me a good look at the shape of the object. the other video clips' i took were of what i think may have been the infrared monitor on the site. this monitor had a wider angle lens, showing me what happened after the object left the first ones' view. in the second, i noticed the it changed its speed, then streaked off at an un-paralleled one. when i viewed the object during this incident i was shocked to see that this thing was absolutely massive, and moving incredibly fast. i was able to conclude this, due to the date and time counter on the bottom left side of the monitors'. i was further shocked that it traveled so close to the surface of the sun and was able to survive two consecutive solar eruptions on a massive scale. i couldn't understand how something so massive was able to move so quickly around the sun and back towards earth. the date and time counter displayed showed that this thing took only 4 days' to reach as far as it did, from around the sun and back. if i am not mistaken its a distance of 93,000,000 miles from the earth to the sun. i just couldn't believe something could move that fast! i lost track of it after it left the second monitor. whatever it was, i went back the following morning to see if the video was still there. the video clip of it streaking off was removed from the site. i witnessed this event on the 27'th, but the counter states the event started back on the 24'th. the object is still visible, but now right before it streaks off, the image is removed and you just see the object moving slowly. its like they are playing it off as a meteor. unfortunately my phone wont allow me to download my videos to the computer, however i do have the evidence in hand and present with me at this very moment. i assure you it is very genuine. i am more than willing to share the video clips in person if it is possible.
content.summary: Was viewing nasa solar observation satelite when i viewd a massive object circling the sun and back towards earth

content.detailedDescription:
Saturday july 6, 2013, 21:41, close to the gadsden mall

after my co-worker and i shut down the store we were in the parking lot about to get in our cars. he and i noticed a yellow-orange orb in the sky. the brightness of the object and that it seemed to be moving higher is what first grabbed our attention.  we watched it for approximately one minute during which time it kept moving and rose higher. when the object did not disappear i got out my phone and started filming. 

the orb moved from south to north and seemed to get higher as it moved. the orb flared to bright red (at 21 seconds on the video), became larger and began to pulsate. the edges became fuzzy looking after the flare. it did not seem to be moving either toward or away from us.

i took a one minute video of the object. it was still glowing and moving when i stopped the camera. my co-worker and i watched the object for another minute or so before getting in our separate cars. i drove north toward my house away from the object so i do not know how much longer it was in the sky.
content.summary: Yellow-orange orb rising in elevation then flaring to red with fuzzy edges. two witnesses and a 1 minute video.

content.detailedDescription: I was sleeping at the time amd awakened by a whish/whispy noise and really thought nothing of it. i found this object several hours later in my backyard. at first, from a distance, i thought it was a mess that an animal had made . when i got closer i saw it was something different i have never seen before. it was broken open on one side with a jelly goo that was pretty solid, with a skeletal looking white object in the gel. the outer shell was leathery to the touch, yes i touched it.  i thought maybe it was a pod type "puff ball" or mushroom growth, then thought that something that size could not have grown that quick( in a few hours) or also maybe it was an aborted egg/embryo from a large bird, just very strange! i slid this object onto a cardboard, took it to the high school science teacher, he had no idea of what it was. i never persued the matter. i kept it frozen for 3 or 4 weeks and it faded in color and eventually deteriorated to a glob.....I threw it out! any ideas what this is/was? is it something natural or from somewhere unknown?
content.summary: Late evening/early morning awoken by whisping sound, payed no attention to it. that moring found weird object in backyard.

content.summary: Unknowingly caught in a photograph of heart castle

content.detailedDescription:
One of the nights while i was vacationing in cancun, mexico i decided to take some night pictures of the resort and the night sky. i decided to try a new technique called exposure to the left that many photographers use to capture the milky way in an area that has a lot of light pollution. exposure to the left focuses on the dark sky verses buildings which are close by and as a result we will have a well lite night sky with all the stars nicely visible because using this technique will absorb all the light possible. 
back to the subject... so i began taking pictures of the night sky adjusting the settings on my dslr playing around to see what would yield the best results. the whole time i was aware of the area in focus and what i wanted to capture in the frame and i would then view the pictures to see the results. well in one of them i noticed 2 blue objects in the sky and when i zoomed in to get a better view i noticed that it was 2 flying objects that appeared to hovering and you can so see the energy that the ufo's are releasing on top and bottom to maintain there position. once again i was not able to see them with the naked eye, but yet my camera was able to using a tripod, iso 200, shutter speed of 20-30 seconds. the trees look a bit blurry because there was a slight wind.
content.summary: Not visible with the naked eye. took a long exposure picture 20-30sec of the night sky

content.detailedDescription:
On june 22, 2014, i was sitting on my private outdoor rooftop in brooklyn, ny, (williamsburg) with a friend of mine. i watch the sky every night - i can usually find mars if it is visible, can identify numerous constellations, know the difference between a satellite and an airplane, and just love to stare out into space. at about 10:17 pm, i was looking at the sky as i always do, but it wasn't a very clear night and very few stars were visible due to the massive light pollution created by the new york city lights. out of the corner of my eye i noticed an orange glowing orb of light. after doing a quick double-take, i saw there were actually three orbs of light moving across the sky in a way i have never seen any craft or airplane or satellite move - ever. it was completely silent and seemed to float through the air. i instantly knew i was seeing a ufo; i had absolutely no doubt in my mind. in the midst of my excitement/awe/disbelief, i grabbed my iphone and tried to record as much as i could (i knew that if i didn't capture this experience no one would ever believe me). the orbs of light moved across the sky and i took my first video but to the blind eye and without the technology needed to slow down the video, all i could see was the black night sky. i had a feeling that nothing was on that video and quickly tried to take another one before it was too late. fortunately,  i was able to switch the camera on in time and record what i did. for two weeks i didn't think i had captured anythng, until i decided to watch the videos on my computer. there is not person who i've showed this to who can come up with any plausible explanation for what i saw and recorded. 

the three orbs of light were moving northeast and started very low - pretty close to some of the taller buildings. as it moved across the sky (in a pretty slow and stable pace) it began to rise in elevation before hovering for about 20 seconds almost directly above the building across the street from me. as it hovered there the lights remained solid and then out of nowhere the 3 lights moved rapidly throughout that area of the sky - not side to side but in terms of elevation. it was hard to determine at first whether the three orbs were all one object or if they were in fact three seperate crafts. after watching the orbs move as they did here, both in unison and independant paths, it was clear that this was one entity. it then descended at an extremely rapid pace and then just vanished. i immediately fell to the ground with tears streaming out of my eyes. i knew what i had just witnessed and was overwhlem with shock, happiness, confimation, fear, confusion, etc. i've always known that other life existed and that ufos regularly visit the earth, but i never in a million years thought i would be lucky enough to witness such an encounter, let alone capture it on video.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: While sitting on my rooftop, which i do nightly, i spotted three orbs of light. these orbs moved seamlessly through the sky before hovering for about half a minute and then moving vast distances in less than one second.

content.summary: I only noticed it from the corner of my eye, a silvery streak traveling across the sky.

content.detailedDescription:
Hello, i was bike riding in santa barbara. when the bike path turned north to merge with a main rode, i stopped for a water break. as i was facing the santa barbara hills, taking a drink, i noticed a lot of straight contrails in the air (common but don't think commercial. by their dissipation most the aircraft had headed north. if military, most likely from point magu nas in the south?) my eyes then caught a "apparently small", white, almond shaped craft, moving south at a pretty good clip; looked to be above the contrails but same altitude as the clouds. it emitted no contrails or sound and it zig-zaged from it's base course very quickly like it was avoiding something in it's path. first "downward" then back "upward" but overshot it's base course and went higher into the sky. unfortunately by they time i got my cell phone ready for pics, the craft was lost behind a tree and denser cloud cover. 

as for me, i thought it was very cool; been looking out for them, to be honest. out of 30 years as an electro-mechanical technician, 15 were in aerospace helping to build satellites. i know all about spacecraft. i also know all about aircraft. i know what both can and cannot do. 
this was obviously a craft moving in a way spacecraft and aircraft cannot.
it was doing it's own thing; oblivious of "our" physics and environmental limitations.
content.summary: Small, almond shaped, white craft. no contrails.
